task.summary: Default task
Changes: * Rewritten some code of HddToEdit in order to simplify the code and make it use less memory. * Removed unnecessary print statements.
Changes: * Partially done 4v removal progress. * Backing up in new branch because this process should later on be resumed.
Changes: * Added ramstick removal from computer in the computer_edit functionality.

Changes: * Updated changelog to about the changes. * Simplified remove_drive_from_computer, remove_observation_from_computer and remove_ramstick_from_computer by moving repeating code to remove_object_from_computer.
Changes: * Added functionality to add empty ramstick. * Found and fixed bug related to saving changed ram type of ramstick. * Updated changelog.
Changes: * Fixed bug where ramstick removal is not present when adding nonexistant ramstick.
Changes: * Removing ramstick updates total_ram based on sum of remaining rams.
Changes: * Automatic ramstick adding functionality. * Updated changelog.
Changes: * Simplified some code, removed unnecessary classes and functions.
Changes: * Trash cleaning of 4th version code and unecessary files.
Changes: * ULCDTinterface cleanup from 4v remains.
Changes: * Updated changelog.md regarding cleanup.

Changes: * rewritten 'ComputerRecord' class's '_save_drives()' method to fit changed data sent via json. * Added 'DriveFamily', 'DriveHeight', 'DriveLength', 'DriveNotes', 'DrivePowerIdle', 'DrivePowerSeek', 'DrivePowerSpin', 'DrivePowerStandby', 'DriveTypes', 'DriveWeight', 'DriveWidth' models. * Changes to 'hdd_edit.html' (view/edit) to reflect changed Drive's model structural changes. * Rewritten some code in 'hddLotsSubTemplate.html', 'hddOrdersSubTemplate.html' and index.js to remove unecessary code. * Added new file 'partial_success.html' which is used when part of work is done, the problematic parts are skipped and user is informed what went wrong and with what. * Changes to logic.py: * Removed unused dependencies. Added new 'django.core.files.uploadedfile.InMemoryUploadedFile' which is used for object identification in 'DriveTextFileManager' class object's initiation. * Update 'LotHolder' class to reflect changed Drive's model structural changes. * Removed 'TarProcessor', 'AlternativeTarProcessor', 'HddOrderProcessor', 'AlternativeHddOrderProcessor'. * Added new classes 'TarProcessor', 'DriveOrderProcessor', 'DriveTextFileManager', 'DriveLineProcessor' to replace removed classes functionality. * changes to views.py and urls.py to better handle exceptions and call changed classes.
Changes: * Updated changelog.md regarding changes of drive functionality expansion.
Changes: * Added missed logic when adding/updating 'Drives' to include data 'total_writes', 'description'.
Changes: * Removed unused class forms UploadFileFrom and DocumentForm. * Added TarDocumentForm(to handle tar validation) and DriveOrderDocumentForm(to handle csv validation).
Changes: * Added explanatory comments to TarDocumentForm and DriveOrderDocumentForm. * Updated changelog.md.
Changes: * returned automatic ramstick adding feature which was lost due to revert on 2019-05-13.
Changes: * Added additional field to search computers by battery model.
Changes: * expanded ability to search by battery model.
Changes: * fixed minor bug. Id was not set right for an element and because of that select/unselect all was not working properly for that <div>.
Changes: * Solved Original not being able to filter.
Changes: * removed some todos, which were allready done.
Changes: * Updated catToSold.html to be compatible with current data.
Changes: * Divided 'All storages', 'Lots', and 'Orders' to other views instead of using Index.

Changes: * Removed Document model as unnecessary. Instead whole validation of tars and logs are being handled by forms 'DriveOrderDocumentForm', 'TarDocumentForm'. * Changed javascript code to use rendered in urls and fixed issue with url formation. * Implemented pagination in '/sold/', /orders/, /chargers/, /drives/, /lots/, /drive_orders/ and /search/'. * Updated changelog.md.
Changes: * Added excel/csv file generation functionality to orders. * Updated changelog.md.
